-- BHP Billiton, Lonmin, Pioneer May Move: South African Stock Market Preview
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a   a n d   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-12-10T06:04:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-09/steinhoff-bhp-billiton-may-move-south-african-market-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in South Africa. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  snapped six
days of gains, falling 152.22, or 0.5 percent, to 31,617.66 at
the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  BHP Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ): The world’s largest mining
company has raised its wage offer for striking workers at the
Hillside aluminum smelter in South Africa to 8.5 percent,
Reuters reported, citing a National Union of Metalworkers
spokesman. BHP Billiton declined for the second day, losing 1.9
rand, to 266.83 rand.  Lonmin Plc  (LON SJ): The resources group and South Africa’s
National Union of Mineworkers failed to resolve a wage dispute
at a meeting with a labor mediator late yesterday, a union
official said. Lonmin was unchanged at 201.80 rand.  Pioneer Food Group Ltd.  (PFG SJ): Halewood International
Plc, a U.K. distributor of wine and spirits, may make an offer
for KWV Holdings Ltd. that exceeds a 12 rand ($1.75) a share-bid
by Pioneer Food Group Ltd., Sake24 said, citing confidential
documents between KWV and Halewood. KWV and Halewood have been
in talks for the past 18 months, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper said. Pioneer dropped 3.80 rand, or 6.6 percent, to 54
rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc  (AAUK US) rose 0.4 percent to $23.62.
 AngloGold Ashanti Ltd . (AU US) added 0.7 percent to $48.37. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) climbed 1.7 percent to $78.09.  DRDGold
Ltd . (DROOY US) fell 0.2 percent to $4.89.  Gold Fields Ltd . (GFI
US) advanced 1.5 percent to $17.80.  Harmony Gold Mining Co . (HMY
US) increased 1.7 percent to $12.37. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) declined 1.1 percent to $31.90.  Sappi Ltd . (SPP US)
slipped 2.1 percent to $5.05.  Sasol Ltd . (SSL US) gained 0.9
percent to $47.90.  To contact the reporter on this story:
